This paper deals with the problem of verifying fairness in machine learning systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive concentration inequalities, which is a statistical technique that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a tool called VeriFair, which could be categorized under the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
